-- Derrick Rose Has 32 Points as Chicago Bulls Defeat New York Knicks 105-102
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-02-03T05:00:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-03/derrick-rose-has-32-points-as-chicago-bulls-defeat-new-york-knicks-105-102.html
Derrick Rose  had 32 points and 13
assists to lead the Chicago Bulls to a 105-102 defeat of the New
York Knicks, who have lost 10 of their last 12 games.  Amar’e Stoudemire, who had 34 points and 11 rebounds to
lead the Knicks (8-14), missed a 3-pointer from the top of the
key with 10 seconds left that would have tied the game.  Carmelo Anthony  added 26 points for the Knicks in the
National Basketball Association game last night at New York’s
Madison Square Garden.  Carlos Boozer and Kyle Korver had 16 points each for the
Bulls (19-6), who have the best record in the Eastern
Conference.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  